.TH "setGroups" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
setGroups \- reset the replication group contained in the domain
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]domain.setGroups(<options>)\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
SdbDomain
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This function is used to reset the replication group contained in the domain.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.PP
User must ensure that the group does not contain any data before deleting a
replication group, otherwise the operation will fail.
.RE
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
options ( \f[I]object, required\f[] )
.PP
Modify the domain attributes through the options parameters:
.IP \[bu] 2
Groups ( \f[I]string/array\f[] ): All replication groups contained in the
domain.
.PP
Format: \f[C]Groups: [\[aq]group1\[aq], \[aq]group2\[aq]]\f[]
.IP \[bu] 2
AutoSplit ( \f[I]boolean\f[] ): Whether the domain is automatically split.
.PP
Format: \f[C]AutoSplit: true | false\f[]
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
When the function executes successfully, there is no return value.
.PP
When the function fails, an exception will be thrown and an error message will
be printed.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
