.SH VERSION
.PP
v2.0 and above
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
Create a domain containing two replication groups, and then turn on automatic
split.
.RS 2
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
> var domain = db.createDomain(\[aq]mydomain\[aq], [\[aq]group1\[aq], \[aq]group2\[aq]], {AutoSplit: true})
\f[]
.fi
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Delete a replication group "group2" from the domain and add another replication
group "group3".
Two replication groups "group1" and "group3" are contained in the domain at
last.
.RS 2
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
> domain.setGroups({Groups: [\[aq]group1\[aq], \[aq]group3\[aq]]})
\f[]
.fi
.RE
